entries.meaning: (mathematics) The fourth power; the square of a square.

verbs.description: biquadrate (third-person singular simple present biquadrates, present participle biquadrating, simple past and past participle biquadrated)

entries.meaning: (transitive, arithmetic) To raise to the fourth power; to determine the result of multiplying by itself three times.
examples: Two biquadrated is equal to sixteen.
